    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nN/A\n\n### Feature description\n\nWe should include the window information in the args table passed to `WinEnter` and especially `WinLeave` autocmd Lua function callbacks. Without this I don't think there is a straightforward way to get the window ID in the `WinLeave` CB (if the buffer IDs are the same, say).\r\n\r\n```\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('WinEnter', {\r\n  pattern = '*',\r\n  callback = function(args) vim.pretty_print(args) end,\r\n})\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('WinLeave', {\r\n  pattern = '*',\r\n  callback = function(args) vim.pretty_print(args) end,\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrent result:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  buf = 10,\r\n  event = \"WinLeave\",\r\n  file = \"/Users/mishchea/dotfiles/nvim/init.vim\",\r\n  id = 14,\r\n  match = \"/Users/mishchea/dotfiles/nvim/init.vim\"\r\n}\r\n{\r\n  buf = 3,\r\n  event = \"WinEnter\",\r\n  file = \"/Users/mishchea/local/share/nvim/runtime/doc/options.txt\",\r\n  id = 13,\r\n  match = \"/Users/mishchea/local/share/nvim/runtime/doc/options.txt\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Proposal:** Include `win = win_id` in the `args` CB for those events. I haven't checked `WinEnter`, `WinScrolled`, etc., but this probably also applies to them.",
    "closed_at": "2023-07-28T05:13:28Z",
